edu.illinois.cs.cogcomp.annotation

Interface AnnotatorService

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    BasicAnnotatorService, CuratorAnnotatorService

    public interface AnnotatorService
    Specifies the operations to be supported by an AnnotatorService, which creates a TextAnnotation from raw text and populates it with views generated by NLP components. Created by mssammon on 9/22/15.

    • Method Detail

      • createBasicTextAnnotation

        TextAnnotation createBasicTextAnnotation(String corpusId,
                                         String docId,
                                         String text)
                                  throws AnnotatorException
        A convenience method for creating a TextAnnotation. Typically, this will be accomplished using a TextAnnotationBuilder.
        Parameters:
        text - The raw text used to build the TextAnnotation where all the Views should be added.
        Throws:
        AnnotatorException - If this service cannot provide this viewName

      • createAnnotatedTextAnnotation

        TextAnnotation createAnnotatedTextAnnotation(String corpusId,
                                             String textId,
                                             String text)
                                      throws AnnotatorException
        A convenience method for creating a TextAnnotation and adding all the Views supported by this AnnotatorService. This amounts to calling createBasicTextAnnotation(String, String, String) and successive calls of addView(edu.illinois.cs.cogcomp.core.datastructures.textannotation.TextAnnotation, String)
        Parameters:
        text - The raw text used to build the TextAnnotation where all the Views should be added.
        Throws:
        AnnotatorException - If none of the viewProviders supports this viewName

      • createAnnotatedTextAnnotation

        TextAnnotation createAnnotatedTextAnnotation(String corpusId,
                                             String textId,
                                             String text,
                                             Set<String> viewNames)
                                      throws AnnotatorException
        An overloaded version of createAnnotatedTextAnnotation(String, String, String) that adds only the Views requested.
        Parameters:
        text - The raw text used to build the TextAnnotation where all the Views should be added.
        viewNames - Views to add
        Throws:
        AnnotatorException - If none of the viewProviders supports this viewName

      • addView

        boolean addView(TextAnnotation ta,
                String viewName)
         throws AnnotatorException
        The standard way of adding a specific View to a TextAnnotation.
        Parameters:
        ta - The TextAnnotation where the View should be added.
        viewName - The name of the View to be added. By convention this has to be a constant in ViewNames.
        Returns:
        'true' if the TextAnnotation was modified by this call.
        Throws:
        AnnotatorException - If this AnnotatorService cannot provide this viewName,
